---
import Footer from "@/components/Footer";
import "../styles/global.css";
import { ArrowLeft } from "lucide-react";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Cookie Policy | MVP Geek</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Cookie Policy for MVP Geek — how we use cookies, tracking technologies, analytics, preferences, and your control over them."
    />
    <meta name="author" content="Rajesh Rajasekaran" />
    <meta name="robots" content="index, follow" />
    <meta name="googlebot" content="index, follow" />
    
    <!-- Canonical URL -->
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://www.mvpgeek.com/" />

    <!-- Favicon -->
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <!-- Fonts -->
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Bricolage+Grotesque:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </head>

  <body
    class="min-h-screen p-8 leading-relaxed bg-[#0D0A08] text-white font-inter"
  >
    <main class="max-w-6xl mx-auto space-y-6 pb-4">
      <a href="/" class="py-2 flex items-center gap-2 text-lg"
        ><ArrowLeft className="ml-2" size={20} />Back</a
      >
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        Cookie Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm opacity-80">Last updated: November 13, 2025</p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        1. What Are Cookies
      </h2>
      <p>
        Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a
        website. They help websites function efficiently, improve user
        experience, remember preferences, and provide analytics to site owners.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        2. How We Use Cookies
      </h2>
      <p>We use cookies for the following purposes:</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        Essential Cookies
      </h3>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Enabling core website functionality</li>
        <li>Authentication & security</li>
        <li>Load balancing and performance</li>
        <li>Remembering your cookie preferences</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        Analytics Cookies
      </h3>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Understanding how users navigate our site</li>
        <li>Tracking page views, sessions, and visitor behavior</li>
        <li>Identifying popular content and features</li>
        <li>Error tracking and performance monitoring</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        Functional Cookies
      </h3>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Remembering language or theme preferences</li>
        <li>Saving form inputs or user settings</li>
        <li>Enabling personalized content</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        Marketing Cookies
      </h3>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Ad personalization and targeting</li>
        <li>Measuring conversions and ad performance</li>
        <li>Social media integrations</li>
        <li>Remarketing across websites</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        3. Types of Cookies We Use
      </h2>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Session Cookies:</strong> expire when you close your browser.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Persistent Cookies:</strong> remain until deleted or expired.
        </li>
        <li><strong>First-Party Cookies:</strong> set directly by MVPGeek.</li>
        <li>
          <strong>Third-Party Cookies:</strong> set by analytics, social media, or
          ad partners.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        4. Third-Party Services
      </h2>
      <p>We work with third-party providers who may set cookies:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Google Analytics:</strong> for traffic and behavior insights.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Social Media Platforms:</strong> Facebook, LinkedIn, X, etc.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Payment Processors:</strong> may set cookies during secure transactions.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        5. Managing Cookies
      </h2>
      <p>You can control cookies in several ways:</p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        Browser Settings
      </h3>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Block all cookies</li>
        <li>Block third-party cookies</li>
        <li>Delete stored cookies</li>
        <li>Receive alerts when cookies are set</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        Cookie Consent Banner
      </h3>
      <p>
        On your first visit, you can choose which cookies to accept or reject.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        Opt-Out Links
      </h3>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Google Analytics Opt-Out</li>
        <li>Facebook Ad Preferences</li>
        <li>Google Ads Settings</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        6. Impact of Disabling Cookies
      </h2>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Some website features may not function properly</li>
        <li>You may need to re-enter information more often</li>
        <li>Personalized experiences may be limited</li>
        <li>Some third-party integrations may not work</li>
        <li>Analytics data may be incomplete</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        7. Cookie Retention
      </h2>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Session cookies:</strong> deleted when the browser closes.
        </li>
        <li><strong>Persistent cookies:</strong> remain 30 days to 2 years.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics cookies:</strong> typically 24–26 months.</li>
        <li><strong>Marketing cookies:</strong> typically 30–90 days.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        8. Updates to This Cookie Policy
      </h2>
      <p>
        We may revise this Cookie Policy to reflect changes in technology, legal
        requirements, or our practices. We will update the "Last updated" date
        accordingly.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold font-[Bricolage Grotesque, sans-serif]">
        9. Contact Us
      </h2>
      <p>If you have any questions, contact us:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1">
        <li>
          Email: <a class="underline text-white" href="mailto:info@mvpgeek.com"
            >info@mvpgeek.com</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          Website: <a
            class="underline text-white"
            href="https://www.mvpgeek.com">mvpgeek.com</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>Response Time: Typically 24–48 hours</li>
      </ul>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
